title: Emily Pedersen holds edge over Becky Morgan at Indian Open
text:
Emily Pedersen holds edge over Becky Morgan at Indian Open 24 Oct 2015 13:31:56 
comments 
Danish rookie Emily Pedersen will take a one-shot lead over Wales' Becky Morgan into the final round of the Hero Women's Indian Open on Sunday. 
Pedersen, 19, is the only player in the field under par after adding a 73 to her opening 70 to finish one under, with Morgan returning a 71 to end the day on level par. 
American Cheyenne Woods, niece of 14-time major winner Tiger Woods, carded a 69 - only the second sub-70 score of the week - to lie three shots off the pace on two over, alongside England's Liz Young. 
Pedersen, who carded two bogeys and one birdie, said: " It could have been better but I'm happy with my score. My game was much better than yesterday. I just didn't hole the putts." 
Italy's Giulia Sergas is four off the lead after carding a triple-bogey eight on the 18th in her 76 and admitted she was " about to chew someone's head off" after leaving the recording area. 
"I went in the water twice," Sergas said. "It was just the wrong club, wrong decision with the first shot and second shot. I'm now plus three, so you never know. If it happened to me it could happen to anybody." Related Sport News
